        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Crafted by layering bamboo with strips of sliced scales harvested from a fire-breathing dragon, this bow has a significant draw strength. This design is commonly seen in Hongal, as the shorter limbs allow for easier maneuvering on horseback. While the wielder of this <em>+2 striking composite shortbow</em> is mounted, they apply the bow's item bonus to Nature checks to Command your mount.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">2</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You draw the bow back to its maximum draw length without nocking an arrow, and as you release the string, the <em>dragonfire halfbow</em> casts @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Fireball] (heightened to 5th-rank; @Check[type:reflex|dc:29] save), targeted at a point of your choosing within the spell's range. You and your mount are immune to the effects of this <em>fireball</em>.</p>"
